<br>
If I pick up an item that will be used for a quest, I keep it. I don't care if the quest is applicable to a cleric or not, because I know at some point I will find someone who needs the items. I dont' know about the rest of you, but my bank is mostly filled with 8 slot toolboxes (that I made because I didn't have the gold for backpacks).  A bank filled with all toolboxes means that I have 16 fewer bank inventory slots than I would &quot;normally&quot; have if it were filled with 10-slot deluxe toolboxes.<br>
<br>
Might I suggest an alternative?<br>
<br>
Have every Sister save one container in her bank for these items and keep a running tally of what we have available here on the boards. Or you might assign one sister to keep track of what everyone has and post it here. The two parties would be responsible for getting together to do the trade, that way the guild banker won't be pulled from pillar to post delivering and picking up items.<br>
<br>
My 2cp<br>
<br>
